burlap.behavior.singleagent.options.model

Class BFSNonMarkovOptionModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • burlap.behavior.singleagent.options.model.BFSMarkovOptionModel
      • burlap.behavior.singleagent.options.model.BFSNonMarkovOptionModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FullModel, SampleModel

    public class BFSNonMarkovOptionModel
extends BFSMarkovOptionModel
    A slightly more memory intensive implementation of BFSNonMarkovOptionModel that can also compute the transitions of non-Markov options. See the java doc for BFSNonMarkovOptionModel for more information on how it computes the model and how to increase performance.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan.
